# CTSecure Changelog

All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

## [v1.0.1] - 2026-02-05

**Stability & usability patch**

- Fixed watchdog false-positive restarts causing port binding conflicts on Windows
- Fixed Ctrl+C shutdown error (`RuntimeError: no current event loop`)
- Added clear startup success banner with ports, time, and usage instructions
- Improved watchdog reliability with real `/metrics` health check
- Added pre-bind port availability check

Recommended upgrade for all Windows users.

## [v1.0.0] - 2026-01-xx (Initial Release)

**First public release**

- Core reverse proxy functionality with multi-domain support
- SSL/TLS support with automatic certificate loading
- WAF (Web Application Firewall) with basic rule set
- Rate limiting & IP banning with real firewall integration
- Cloudflare compatibility (header trust & IP filtering)
- GeoIP blocking (optional)
- Blacklist persistence & auto-cleanup
- GUI configuration editor (PyQt6)
- TUI real-time monitoring panel
- Prometheus metrics endpoint (`/metrics`)
- Logging with JSON format & daily rotation
- Windows-compatible startup & graceful shutdown

Initial version focused on security, ease of use, and cross-platform stability.